books.Title: Happy Sugar Life
books.Description: The series is centered on high school girl Satō Matsuzaka who befriends a mysterious little girl named Shio, who was abandoned by her mother, and immediately becomes highly attached to Satō. They both agree to live together in Satō's apartment, and the former vows to protect that feeling of love, even if it means committing crimes or even killing people.
books.Author: Tomiyaki Kagisora

books.Title: Shimoneta: A Boring World Where the Concept of Dirty Jokes Doesn't Exist
books.Description: In the dystopian future of 2030, the Japanese government is cracking down on any perceived immoral activity from using risqué language to distributing lewd materials in the country, to the point where all citizens are forced to wear high-tech devices called Peace Makers (PM) at all times that analyze every spoken word and hand motions for any action that could break the law.
books.Author: Hirotaka Akagi

books.Title: Sayings of Confucius
books.Description: Philosophical text composed of sayings and ideas attributed to Confucius and his contemporaries
books.Author: Disciples of Confucius

books.Title: 7 Billion Needles
books.Description: The story revolves around Hikaru Takabe, a reclusive teenage girl who is secretly a host to being known as Horizon, in search of an intergalactic murderer intent on killing humanity.
books.Author: Nobuaki Tadano

books.Title: Tokyo Mew Mew
books.Description: Story focuses on five girls infused with the DNA of endangered animals which gives them special powers and allows them to transform into 'Mew Mews'.
books.Author: Reiko Yoshida

books.Title: Lord of the World
books.Description: Story about reign of the Antichrist, which is enabled by a movement towards global peace and the unification of religious and political thought.
books.Author: Robert Hugh Benson

books.Title: Brave New World
books.Description: Largely set in a futuristic World State, whose citizens are environmentally engineered into an intelligence-based social technology.
books.Author: Aldous Huxley

books.Title: Island
books.Description: It's the account of Will Farnaby, a cynical journalist who is shipwrecked on the fictional island of Pala.
books.Author: Aldous Huxley

books.Title: Dog Nigga
books.Description: Rex is a half man half dog. He was created when a drunk old man forced himself on a stray female dog in the street. Because of that he has to live his life as a freak rejected by society.
